name: Chocotrice Easter Card
description:
Chocotrice
Common in Switzerland, a chocotrice is hatched from an abandoned easter egg incubated beneath a rabbit. The Chocotrice is an incredibly dangerous animal. From the moment it is born it is able to turn any living thing to chocolate with a single glance.

name: Sham Roc St. Patrick's Day Card
description:
Send a reminder of the true meaning of St. Patrick's Day with this original 4.25" by 5.5" folded card.
Printed on Gmund Bier Paper, Lager (a recycled paper which contains beer making ingredients and old beer labels).
Comes with French Paper Pop-tone, Gumdrop Green envelope.
Front reads:
Sham Roc
These enormous, reclusive, birds spend the majority of the year nesting in remote areas of the Irish moors. In the spring, sham rocs fly far from their nesting grounds in search of partygoers. When a sham roc finds a party, it swoops down, carrying a keg off in its claws.

Note: Image is only an approximation, colors may vary in printed card.

name: Cupicabra Valentine's Day Card
description:
This 4.25" by 5.5" folded Valentine's card, with original cryptozoological design is printed on Stardream Opal 105 lb. card stock. Complete with red envelope.
Front Reads:
Cupicabra
Living in supermarkets and candy stores, the cupicabra throws gold-tipped arrows to hunt its prey, heart-shaped candy boxes. It then sucks out the chocolate filling, leaving nothing but mangled packaging. Anyone pricked by these arrows feels an intense craving for either love or candy.

name: Jackibou Christmas Card
description:
A whimsical 4.25" by 5.5" card with blank back featuring an original animal design, comes with black metallic envelope.
Front reads:
Jackibou
Related to the jackalope, the jackibou is a rare creature that is seen only in winter. While its white coat camouflages it in snowy environments, it has been known to collect brightly colored objects in its antlers, particularly during the month of December.

Only 5 left!
